  "title": "refactor(pagination): First try on the BEM naming of a widget",
  "body": "I added BEM naming to the pagination widget. The generated markup\nlooks like:\n\n``` html\n<ul class=\"ais-pagination\">\n  <li class=\"ais-pagination--item ais-pagination--item-first ais-pagination--item__disabled\"><a href=\"#\">First</a></li>\n  <li class=\"ais-pagination--item ais-pagination--item-previous ais-pagination--item__disabled\"><a href=\"#\">Previous</a></li>\n  <li class=\"ais-pagination--item ais-pagination--item-page ais-pagination--item-page__active\"><a href=\"#\">1</a></li>\n  <li class=\"ais-pagination--item ais-pagination--item-page\"><a href=\"#\">2</a></li>\n  <li class=\"ais-pagination--item ais-pagination--item-page\"><a href=\"#\">3</a></li>\n  <li class=\"ais-pagination--item ais-pagination--item-page\"><a href=\"#\">4</a></li>\n  <li class=\"ais-pagination--item ais-pagination--item-page\"><a href=\"#\">5</a></li>\n  <li class=\"ais-pagination--item ais-pagination--item-next\"><a href=\"#\">Last</a></li>\n  <li class=\"ais-pagination--item ais-pagination--item-last\"><a href=\"#\">Last</a></li>\n</ul>\n```\n\nEverytime I add a `BEM` class, one can add its own set of custom\nclasses through the `cssClasses` object config in the widget.\nA default `pagination.css` file is provided but currently only\nincludes the `visibility:hidden` styling of disabled elements. The\ndemo styling is thus done through bootstrap classes.\n\nI quite happy with the end result. I also simplified the existing code\nin the process and moved all default attributes in the widget (instead\nof the components).\n\nI'm submitting the PR to get feedback and then I'll update the docs\nand maybe add some default styling not from Bootstrap.\n",
